                        Q d.f. p-value
Between groups   54872.43    5       0
# meta notes
# common effects model: I^2
# random effects model: Tau
# I2='proportion of total variation in study estimates that is due to heterogeneity' -  Quantifying heterogeneity in a meta-analysis, doi.org/10.1002/sim.1186
# Tau='betweenstudy variance component (^2)'
# Tau estimation via maximum-likelihood: Viechtbauer, W. (2005). Bias and Efficiency of Meta-Analytic Variance Estimators in the Random-Effects Model. Journal of Educational and Behavioral Statistics, 30(3), 261293. https://doi.org/10.3102/10769986030003261

